<title>SWITZERLAND: Adia AGM agrees capital hike for merger.</title>
<headline>Adia AGM agrees capital hike for merger.</headline>
<dateline>LAUSANNE, Switzerland 1996-08-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shareholders of Swiss temporary employment firm Adia SA approved an increase in capital to prepare for a planned merger with French firm Ecco SA to create a new firm Adecco SA.</p>
<p>Shareholders voted in favour of a nominal capital increase of 95,347,000 Swiss francs at a special annual general meeting.</p>
<p>The increase involves issuance of shares worth a nominal 10 Swiss francs, priced at issue at 43.23 Swiss francs.</p>
<p>The measure will raise a total of 412,185,081 Swiss francs.</p>
<p>The new firm will be rival in size U.S.-based Manpower Inc.</p>
<p>-- Zurich Newsroom, +41-1-631 7340</p>
